description.narrative: The objectives of the Project are to: (a) provide the rural areas of the Participating Provinces with reliable electric supply in a sustainable manner through the use of renewable energy; (b) advance the reform of the Borrower#s energy sector in particular critical areas; (c) support the Borrower#s strategy to expand the participation of the private sector in the provision of electricity in the rural areas of the Participating Provinces, as well as strengthen the capacity of Participating Provinces to regulate such participation; and (d) support the creation of sustainable business operations for rural energy in Argentina.

comment.narrative: The still low number of installations relative to the end target is a result of delays of various types, including the 17 monthsittook the project to become effective, adverse weather conditions, difficulties importing equipments and problems locating theoriginally identified beneficiaries requiring to update the lists. The number of installations is now rapidly increasing followingthe initial leadtime and difficulties (as we can see that it went from 0 to 7,744 in twelve months). Furthermore, this number doesnot reflect an additional number of systems that have already been installed but have not yet been certified. The project isexpected to largely achieve this target by project closing

title.narrative: Total number of households served by PERMER (PERMER AF)

comment.narrative: The still low number of installations relative to the end target is a result of delays of various types, including the 17 monthsittook the project to become effective, adverse weather conditions, difficulties importing equipments and problems locating theoriginally identified beneficiaries requiring to update the lists. The number of installations is now rapidly increasing followingthe initial leadtime and difficulties (as we can see that it went from 0 to 7744 in twelve months). Furthermore, this number doesnot reflect an additional number of systems that have already been installed but have not yet been certified. With the increasingmonthly installations rates and the extension of the contracts we expect the project to closely approach the target by the end of2012.
There was demand from Salta and other province for mini-grids. However, due to the high demand in solar home systems from theprovinces, no more funds are available for mini-grids.

title.narrative: Installed SHS in public buildings (PERMER AF)

comment.narrative: This has been delayed for various reasons. A significant increase is expected by the time of the next supervision mission.
